r": "f5f1fd", "default": false, "description": "Category: A feature request, i.e: not implemented / a PR."}], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 6, "created_at": "2018-06-22T07:00:48Z", "updated_at": "2018-06-27T20:38:57Z", "closed_at": "2018-06-27T20:38:57Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "This is exactly in the same domain as `str::from_utf8` except that it uses one character only. Also, this should exist since `char::encode_utf8` does.\r\nThe other functions (`from_utf8_mut`, `from_boxed_utf8`, etc.) should (if appropriate)\r\nbe implemented.\r\n\r\nAn implementation of this is provided below:\r\n```rust\r\nfn from_utf8(a: &[u8]) -> Result<char, Utf8Error> {\r\n    let s = ::std::str::from_utf8(a)?;\r\n    s.chars().next().unwrap()\r\n}\r\n\r\nunsafe fn from_utf8_unchecked(a: &[u8]) -> char {\r\n    let s = ::std::str::from_utf8_unchecked(a);\r\n    s.chars().next().unwrap()\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI don't believe an RFC is needed; if so, please tell me.\r\nedit: make `from_utf8_unchecked` unsafe", "closed_by": {"login": "anirudhb", "id": 9709011, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDkwMTE=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/9709011?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/anirudhb", "html_url": "https://github.com/anirudhb", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/anirudhb/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/anirudhb/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/anirudhb/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/anirudhb/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/anirudhb/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/anirudhb/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/anirudhb/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/anirudhb/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.githu